OwnableInvalidOwner(address).details: The owner is not a valid owner account. (eg. `address(0)`)

OwnableUnauthorizedAccount(address).details: The caller account is not authorized to perform an operation.

CellRevealed(address,uint8,uint8,bool).details: Emitted when a cell revealed by `player` using `revealCell` is successfully decrypted by the Gateway.      `victory` indicates whether the player won the game with this reveal. If `cellIndex` equals 9 then      the player lost the game.

acceptOwnership().details: The new owner accepts the ownership transfer.

boardOf(address).details: Returns the encrypted game board of the current game played by the specified `player`.      The board is stored on a single 256bits integer.

getClearCache256x4().details: Returns the caller's clear cache consisting of two 256-bit blocks.      Each block contains 64 packed 4-bit values, allowing efficient storage and retrieval of small data entries.

returns.block0: The first 256-bit clear block with packed 4-bit values.
returns.block1: The second 256-bit clear block with packed 4-bit values.

params.cellIndex: The index of the cell to retrieve.

returns.clearCell: A value representing the cell content:         - 08: Number of neighboring bombs.         - 9: Cell contains a bomb.

getDebugClearCellsPlusOne(address,uint8).details: DEBUG=true. Helper to identify potential bug in the `_clearCache256x4` mapping

getEncryptedCache256x4().details: DEBUG=true. Returns the caller's encrypted cache consisting of two 256-bit blocks.      Each block contains 64 packed 4-bit values, allowing efficient storage and retrieval of small data entries.

returns.eBlock0: The first 256-bit encrypted block with packed 4-bit values.
returns.eBlock1: The second 256-bit encrypted block with packed 4-bit values.

params.cellIndex: The index of the cell to verify.
params.player: The address of the player whose game board is being checked.

returns._0: `true` if the cell has been decrypted; otherwise, `false`.

params.firstCellIndex: The index of the first cell to be revealed on the board.
params.inputHandle: An fhEVM handle to the input data that contains the encrypted board.
params.inputProof: The fhEVM proof used to verify the validity of the encrypted board.
params.player: The address of the player who will play the game.

newGame(uint8,uint8).details: Validates the `firstCellIndex` to ensure it's within bounds, and then creates a new game board      based on the selected difficulty and mode (deterministic or random). The game is then initialized      for the caller.

params.firstCellIndex: The index of the first cell to be revealed at the start of the game.                        The index must be within the valid range of the board.
params.level: The difficulty level that influences the number of `1`s on the board.              - level 0: ~9% of cells will be `1`              - level 1: ~14% of cells will be `1`              - level 2: ~20% of cells will be `1`

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

returns.cellIndexPlusOne: The requested cell index plus one.         - > 0: A cell decryption request is pending (awaiting the gateway's response).         - 0: No active decryption request.
returns.expired: `true` if the decryption request has expired; otherwise, `false`.
returns.maxBlockTimestamp: The block timestamp after which the request expires.

pendingOwner().details: Returns the address of the pending owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

resign().details: Does not revert if the caller has no active game.

revealCell(uint8).details: Reverts if:      - The caller has no active game in progress.      - The caller has already lost the game.      - The `cellIndex` is out of bounds.      - The cell has already been decrypted by the gateway.      - The cell has already been requested for decryption and the request is still pending (not expired).

params.cellIndex: The index of the cell to reveal.

transferOwnership(address).details: Starts the ownership transfer of the contract to a new account. Replaces the pending transfer if there is one. Can only be called by the current owner. Setting `newOwner` to the zero address is allowed; this can be used to cancel an initiated ownership transfer.

DEBUG.details: DEBUG = `true`, the contract is compiled in debug mode.      DEBUG = `false`, the contract is compiled in release mode.

_ZERO_EU256.details: Encrypted 256 bits zero (uint256), precomputed for efficiency.

_ZERO_EU4.details: Encrypted 4 bits zero (uint4), precomputed for efficiency.

_ZERO_EU8.details: Encrypted 8 bits zero (uint8), precomputed for efficiency.

_clearCache256x4.details: Caches the cells successfully revealed and decrypted by a player in their current game.      Cells are encoded in 4-bit values, packed into 256-bit integers (64 cells per uint256).      For an 11x11 grid (121 cells), the cache uses 2 uint256 blocks.      Cell encoding:      - 0: Not decrypted      - 1: Empty (no neighboring bombs)      - 29: Number of neighboring bombs (18)      - 10: Bomb

_debugClearCellsPlusOne.details: DEBUG=true. Helper to identify potential bug in the `_clearCache256x4` mapping

_deterministic.details: If true, game boards are generated deterministically (debug only).

_deterministicGameCount.details: Total number of deterministically generated games (debug only).

_games.details: Tracks the current game associated with each player address. A player can play one game at a time.

_playerToRequestIDPlusOne.details: Maps each player to their active decryption request ID (`requestID + 1`) to distinguish valid      requests from null values.

_requestIDPlusOneToRequest.details: Tracks Gateway decryption request IDs.      Since `requestID` starts at zero, we store `requestID + 1` to distinguish an existing request      from a null (zero) value.

deterministic().notice: Returns `true` if future games will be deterministically generated (debug only).

deterministicGameCount().notice: Returns the total number of deterministically generated games (debug only).

gatewayDelayInSec().notice: Returns constant Gateway callback delay in seconds.

getClearCell(uint8).notice: Returns the decrypted value of the cell at `cellIndex` in the `player`'s current game board.         Reverts if:         - The caller is not an active player (no game in progress).         - The player has already lost the game.         - The cell has not been decrypted by the Gateway (no cached value).

getFirstCellIndex().notice: Returns the index of the first cell selected by the player to reveal at the start of the game.         To prevent an instant loss, this selected cell is automatically cleared of any bombs.

isClearCellAvailable(address,uint8).notice: Returns `true` if the cell at `cellIndex` in the `player`'s current game board has been decrypted         by the Gateway.

isDebug().notice: Returns `true` if the contract is compiled in debug mode; otherwise `false`.

isItAVictory().notice: Returns `true` if the caller has won its game

isItGameOver().notice: Returns `true` if the caller has lost its game

isPlayer(address).notice: Returns `true` if the `player` is a registered player.

moves().notice: Returns a 256-bit integer representing all the cells picked by the caller so far.         Each bit corresponds to a cell: if the bit is set, the cell has been revealed via `revealCell`;         if the bit is not set, the cell has not been picked yet.         Note that if the bit is set, it does not necessarily mean the cell has been decrypted.

newCustomGame(address,uint8,bytes32,byte.notice: Sets the `player`'s game board using an encrypted board created and sent by another account.         This is used for the Challenge mode, where a pre-generated board is provided for the player.         Reverts if the `player` has a game in progress.

newGame(uint8,uint8).notice: Starts a new game for the caller, setting up a board based on the specified difficulty level         and first cell index. The board is generated either deterministically or randomly depending         on the current mode.

pendingDecryptionRequest().notice: Returns information about the caller's current cell decryption request.

playerHasGameInProgress(address).notice: Returns `true` if the `player` has an active game in progress, `false` otherwise.

resign().notice: Allows the caller to resign from their current active game.

revealCell(uint8).notice: Reveals the cell at `cellIndex` in the caller's game board.Important:         If the caller previously requested a cell decryption that has since expired, a new decryption         request will be sent using the **previous cell index** instead of the provided `cellIndex`.         This prevents the player from canceling a prior move by selecting a different cell after the         request expiration.

setDeterministicMode(bool).notice: Allows the owner to enable or disable deterministic game generation mode.         This flag controls whether future games will be generated deterministically (debugging only).

size().notice: Returns the Minesweeper board dimensions.         Board size is fixed and not customizable in the current implementation.
